Vietnam will resettle 300,000 people onstate farms known as new economic zones in 1987, to create jobsand grow more high-value export crops, the communist partynewspaper Nhan Dan said.    Yesterday's edition, received here today, said Vietnamwould invest one billion dong, including the costs ofrelocation, in 272 new economic zones. About one third of thatsum would be spent on export crops such as coffee, tea, rubberand pepper in the Central Highlands, it said.    Since 1975, Vietnam has resettled about three millionpeople from cities and crowded river deltas to the zones. REUTER&#3;